File: platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.ts, lines 15-34 (httpStatusToToolError function).

The current catch-all at line 33 handles ALL remaining non-ok status codes as category='internal', retryable=false. This is wrong for:
- 400 Bad Request → should be category='validation' (semantic match)
- 408 Request Timeout → should be category='timeout', retryable=true (server says try again)
- 422 Unprocessable Entity → should be category='validation' (semantic match)

Add these three cases before the catch-all return at line 33:
```
if (status === 400 || status === 422) {
  return ToolError.validation(message);
}
if (status === 408) {
  return ToolError.timeout(message);
}
```

For tests: add /error-400, /error-408, /error-422 endpoints to the test HTTP server in platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.test.ts (follow the pattern of existing /error-* endpoints around lines 46-86). Add test cases in the fetchFromPage describe block verifying the correct ToolError properties for each.

File: platform/plugin-sdk/src/timing.ts, line 30 (sleep function).

Current implementation:
```
export const sleep = (ms: number): Promise<void> => new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));
```

Add an optional second parameter with the same abort pattern used by retry's internal abortableSleep (lines 51-68 in the same file). Export a SleepOptions interface:
```
export interface SleepOptions {
  signal?: AbortSignal;
}
```

Change the signature to:
```
export const sleep = (ms: number, opts?: SleepOptions): Promise<void> => {
  const signal = opts?.signal;
  if (!signal) return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));
  if (signal.aborted) return Promise.reject(signal.reason instanceof Error ? signal.reason : new DOMException('sleep aborted', 'AbortError'));
  return new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {
    const timer = setTimeout(() => {
      signal.removeEventListener('abort', onAbort);
      resolve();
    }, ms);
    const onAbort = () => {
      clearTimeout(timer);
      reject(signal.reason instanceof Error ? signal.reason : new DOMException('sleep aborted', 'AbortError'));
    };
    signal.addEventListener('abort', onAbort, { once: true });
  });
};
```

Update the SleepOptions export in platform/plugin-sdk/src/index.ts alongside the existing RetryOptions and WaitUntilOptions exports.

Tests: platform/plugin-sdk/src/timing.test.ts — add tests in the sleep describe block.

